      "solution": "// Input\nconst time = readline();\n\n// Parse\nconst re = /(\\d{1,2}):(\\d{1,2}):(\\d{1,2}) (\\wM)/;\nconst r = time.match(re);\nconst dHours = parseInt(r[1]);\nconst dMinutes = parseInt(r[2]);\nconst dSeconds = parseInt(r[3]);\nconst dPeriod = r[4];\n\n// Convert all to seconds since clock was adjusted\nlet passed = (((dHours - 8) * 60) + dMinutes) * 60 + dSeconds;\nif ((dPeriod === 'PM' && dHours < 12) || (dPeriod === 'AM' && dHours === 12)) {\n    passed += 12 * 60 * 60;\n} else if (dHours < 8) {\n    passed += 24 * 60 * 60;\n}\nlet delay = Math.floor(passed / 239); // 4 minutes - 1 second\npassed += delay;\n\n// Back to time\nlet cSeconds = passed % 60;\npassed -= cSeconds;\nlet cMinutes = (passed / 60) % 60;\nlet cHours = (Math.floor(passed - cMinutes * 60) / 3600 + 8) % 24;\nlet period;\n\n// AM/PM\nif (cHours === 12) {\n    period = ' PM';\n} else if (cHours === 0) {\n    cHours = 12;\n    period = ' AM';\n} else if (cHours > 12) {\n    cHours -= 12;\n    period = ' PM';\n} else {\n    period = ' AM';\n}\nconst correctTime = cHours + ':' + formatMS(cMinutes) + ':' + formatMS(cSeconds) + period;\n\n// Output\nconsole.log(correctTime);\n\n// Formatter util\nfunction formatMS(n) {\n  return n.toString().padStart(2,'0')\n}",
      "statement": "The old clock in the railway station is too ancient to be refurbished but too nice to be replaced with a modern one.\nBut it is a little slow. To be precise, <<every four minutes it goes behind by one more second>>.\n\nThe clock is stable in its delay. In addition the station administrator adjusts the clock <<daily at 8AM>>.\nSo it's not that bad.\nBut still all the train events recorded in the official station log are timewise wrong.\n\nYou need to create a script to recover <<true times>> having <<times observed from the station clock>> as input.\n\nPlease note, you don't need to worry about fractions of a second (all tests are guaranteed to have whole seconds for both <<observed>> and <<true>> times).",
